# Open-Source Repository Hygiene

This is a public open-source repository. All organization-specific values MUST be externalized.

## 1. No Hardcoded Emails or Identities

Never embed email addresses, usernames, Slack user IDs, or team distribution lists in source code. Use environment variables, Helm values, or ConfigMap entries. Set defaults to empty string, not a real address.

Pattern: `os.environ.get("SOME_EMAIL", "")` -- production value goes in GitOps overlay, not source.

## 2. No Hardcoded Hostnames or URLs

Never embed organization-specific hostnames (Slack workspaces, GitLab instances, internal domains) in source code. Use environment variables with generic fallback defaults.

Pattern: `os.environ.get("SLACK_WORKSPACE_DOMAIN", "app.slack.com/client")` -- the default works for any Slack workspace.

## 3. No Hardcoded Secrets or Tokens

API tokens, passwords, and credentials go in Kubernetes Secrets referenced via `secretKeyRef` in Helm templates. Never write values to source files, even in comments.

## 4. Helm Values as the Configuration Boundary

The `values.yaml` file defines the configuration surface. All deployment-specific values are overridden in the GitOps ArgoCD application (`darwin-blackboard.yaml`), never in source code.

If a value is specific to one deployment (email, hostname, sheet ID, channel ID), it belongs in Helm values with an empty default.
